<p>Amazon Web Services (AWS) is the world’s most comprehensive and broadly adopted cloud platform, offering over 200 fully featured services from data centers globally. Launched in 2006, it provides on-demand infrastructure, platform, and software services (IaaS, PaaS, SaaS) on a pay-as-you-go basis. Key services include computing power (EC2), storage (S3), and databases (RDS), enabling, secure, scalable, and cost-effective IT solutions for startups, enterprises, and government agencies.
    
</p>

<p>DevOps is a software development methodology that integrates development (Dev) and operations (Ops) teams to improve collaboration, automate workflows, and accelerate the software delivery lifecycle. It emphasizes continuous integration (CI), continuous delivery (CD), and automation to ensure faster, more reliable software releases.
    
</p>


